          content: "The Gujarat government has taken another significant step toward sustainable urban mobility by expanding its fleet of electric buses across major cities, including Ahmedabad, Surat, Vadodara, and Rajkot.\n\nThe initiative aims to reduce carbon emissions, improve air quality, and offer residents a modern and eco-friendly mode of transportation. The newly introduced buses are equipped with air conditioning, GPS tracking, CCTV cameras, digital display systems, and comfortable seating to enhance passenger safety and convenience.\n\nTransport department officials stated that electric buses produce zero tailpipe emissions and operate with significantly lower noise levels compared to conventional diesel-powered vehicles. This transition is expected to contribute to cleaner urban environments while reducing long-term fuel and maintenance costs.\n\nCharging infrastructure is also being developed at major bus depots to support the growing electric vehicle fleet. Fast-charging stations have been installed to ensure buses can return to service quickly, minimizing operational downtime.\n\nDaily commuters have welcomed the initiative, praising the improved comfort, quieter rides, and environmentally friendly transportation option. Authorities believe the expansion will encourage more people to use public transport, helping reduce traffic congestion in urban areas.\n\nOfficials further stated that additional electric buses will be introduced in phases over the coming years as part of Gujarat's long-term sustainable transport strategy. The government continues to invest in green mobility projects to build cleaner, smarter, and more efficient cities for future generations.",
